I wish everyone would just leave their faces alone. Started watching YouTube for makeup tutorials, because I was awful at makeup. It’s now become a saturated “keeping up with the Jones’s” and fake beauty ideals. Makes me sad. I realize I’m probably the only one who feels like this, but it’s a shame all of these YouTubers are unhappy with their natural features.

I think getting fillers that suit YOUR face is great if the person wants it, but I agree that many people do it to the point that they all look the same. I also understand preventive botox, but you have to be careful with that obvi too. I think (yes, very subjective) Nicole didn't need the cheek fillers at all, but I think the jaw filler actually compliments her face shape. I don't understand why someone would like to do a whole new feature on their face, like someone with really thin lips wants to change their entire lips to look like someone else's. The best work is that you yourself can see, and feel better because of it, but other people don't actually really even notice, like getting modest lip fillers that suit your face, so it still looks like you. To me that is the same as makeup, it's you but "improved" (if that is what you want to see on yourself). I wish everyone would think about themselves as individuals and try to see their unique features as something that is beautiful and only compliment those features, and not try to create entirely new ones (Nose job so the new nose doesn't even remotely resemble your old nose, fillers to sculpt entirely new cheek bones)

Hi girl I’m going to give you my honest opinion. I’m dental assist with experience of 22 years, I have 8 veneers on the top and my natural teeth on the bottom. There’s few things you need to know. Make sure you Align your teeth with braces as necessary because your bite has to be perfect to support any dental work. Bleach your teeth and make sure that you stop the bleaching at least a week before they prepare your teeth for veneers. DO NOT MAKE THE MISTAKE!!! Of choosing a shade “color” too light because you are going to be force to bleach the rest of your teeth pretty often to make them match with the veneers,got my point? And I know you like coffee. When you prep teeth for veneer the front and the side have to be reduced in order to look natural. There is thing that you are not going to be able to eat why because they are a thin layer of porcelain they can fracture,they can come loose-with time/years but they can look amazing!!!! If you would like to com6act me feel free I can show mines. Do a Lot of research first and get more than one opinion.
